            <div type="a">
                <column>1</column>
                <head>The Wheat Crop</head>
                <origin/>
                <commentary/>
                <excerpt/>
                <transcript/>
                <trailer/>
                <names/>
                <summary>Rust has caused much greater damage than expected. Abundant wheat crop in
                    Augusta County appears unlikely.</summary>
            </div>
            <div type="a">
                <column>2</column>
                <head>Female Schools in Staunton</head>
                <origin/>
                <commentary/>
                <excerpt>We believe the principle upon which they are founded is correct. Education
                    to be really valuable must be based on religion, and there can be no proper
                    religious instruction where different sects meet in the same class room.</excerpt>
                <transcript/>
                <trailer/>
                <names/>
                <summary>Brief discussion of Virginia Institute and Wesleyan Institute.</summary>
            </div>
