                </names>
                <summary>County Levy for 1858 as of 6/30/1858: $15,198.75. Larger amount than usual,
                    primarily due to additional outlays for Sheriff Turk's expenditures.</summary>
            </div>
            <div type="a">
                <column>3</column>
                <head>Disordered State of Affairs in Kansas.</head>
                <origin/>
                <commentary/>
                <excerpt/>
                <transcript/>
                <trailer/>
                <names/>
                <summary>Government unable to contain internal disorder. Settlers continue to fight
                    over constitution.</summary>
            </div>
